          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Monitoring America's Premiums Act of 2017 or the MAP Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the National Flood Insurance Act of 1968 to suspend annual mandatory flood insurance premium increases for a property in a special flood hazard area during any period the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is revising or updating the flood insurance rate map for that property.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-10-26T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
